track_notes: This summit requires crossing the Red Deer River so it is best done when the water level is low.  After crossing the river follow the south bank upstream to a drainage which you will follow all the way to the ridge known as Dogrib Ridge.  From there it is a ridge walk to the summit.  An ambitious person would be able to do both HC-347 and HC-358 for a double activation, both accessible from the ridge.  I have left both my up track and down track because both are good options depending on the snow/weather conditions.  Cell phone service was not available at the summit.  It should be noted that there are certainly better routes than my chosen route.  There are horse trails toward Sheep Cliffs which can be followed easily and then up an easy ridge to the summit.  A track can be found by searching Jap Mountain on www.explor8tion.com.
